article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 55, Toledo 47
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio -- Kenny Hayes scored 14 points and Anthony Ballard 13 to lead Miami (Ohio), which came on strong in the second half for a 55-47 victory over Toledo on Wednesday night. The RedHawks (11-13, 8-3 Mid-American Conference), who moved into a tie with idle Akron for second in the league's East Division, a game behind Kent State, trailed 21-18 after a first half in which they shot 32 percent (8-for-25). Miami found the range in the second, however, shooting 68.8 percent (11-for-16) to get past the Rockets (3-22, 0-11). Ballard made all four of his second-half shots. Justin Anyijong led the Rockets with 16 points, 13 in the first half, but he was 0-for-4 from the field in the second. After a first half in which neither team made a free throw, with Miami missing the only two attempts awarded, the RedHawks were 14-for-22 from the line in the second half and Toledo 9-for-10.
